I’ve got the patch shape: remove all constructor-time external calls, move protocol address discovery behind a guarded lazy initializer, and switch the candidate list from storage writes to pure indexed lookups. That should fix the `setUp()` deployment revert without changing the exploit path or the profit accounting.
